  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0b9e\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2 \u0b9a\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b85\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Attempting to stop youth protests with emergency law will lead country to mass destruction - Mujibur warns",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "How can it be justified to find and prosecute the plaintiffs for causing damage to the Alarm Hall and the President's House without establishing the law against those who have damaged Parliament's property.",
        "Also, opposition party member Mujibur Rahman said that if we try to stop the struggle of the youth by implementing the Emergency Act, it will lead to massive destruction of the country.",
        "He mentioned this in his speech while participating in the debate on the motion to obtain the approval of the Parliament for the emergency law that was held in the Parliament today.",
        "The government has started the process of arresting youths for causing damage to government property.",
        "Steps are being taken to file a case against them. But during the 52-day government in 2018, the House did not enforce the law against those who damaged government property.",
        "So I ask what is wrong in fighting to establish the rule of law in the country outside the Parliament.",
        "Also on that day the royal emblem on the Speaker's seat in the Parliament was damaged. They broke the speaker's microphone.",
        "Officers' seats were vandalized. Parliamentary property is also state property. But why not prosecuted against them? Deal politics is the reason for this.",
        "Maithripala Sirisena was the President and Mahinda Rajapaksh was the Prime Minister. Ranil Wickramasinghe was the Leader of the Opposition. Their deal politics is the reason why they have not been prosecuted yet.",
        "Also, when Ranil Wickramasinghe addressed this House last April, he said that it is normal for the people to surround the Parliament if no action is taken to find a solution to the people's problem.",
        "Similarly, when he was appointed as the Prime Minister, he was saying in and outside the Parliament that he would protect Kottagama and appoint his party's vice-president Ruvan Wijewardena. But now, after becoming the President, he is acting differently",
        "Also, if we try to stop the struggle of the youth by enforcing the untimely law, it will lead to massive destruction of the country. He said that it should not be forgotten that the leaders of the country in the past went to the underworld due to such decisions."
      ],
